| 2016 | 12.4 | 35.5 | 15.3 | 33.1 | 44.8 | 34.8 |

* This is the weighted average for children in government and private schools only.

In most states, children are expected to do 2-digit division by Std V. Table 9 shows the proportion of children in Std V and Std VIII who can do division. This figure is a proxy for "grade level" arithmetic for Std V and Std VIII. Data for children enrolled in government schools and private schools is shown separately.

